## Interface: 120005, 50503, 20505, 11508, 120007
## Title: Cairn-Demo
## Notes: Live, browseable showcase of every NON-GUI Cairn library. /cdemo opens a tabbed window with one tab per library (Callback, Events, Log, DB, Settings, Addon, Slash, EditMode, Locale, Hooks, Sequencer, Timer, FSM, Comm) plus a Smoke Test tab that PASS/FAIL-asserts every public API. Companion to Cairn-Gui-Demo-2.0 which covers the GUI side.
## Author: ChronicTinkerer
## Version: 1
## Dependencies: Cairn
## SavedVariables: CairnDemoDB
## X-Category: Development Tools
## X-License: MIT
## DefaultState: enabled
## LoadOnDemand: 0

# Core: init, slash command, root Window + TabGroup shell. Each Tabs/*.lua
# below builds out one tab against the shared shell.
Core.lua

# Code-snippet strings shared across tabs (so each tab file stays focused
# on rendering, not on quoting itself in Lua).
Snippets.lua

# Tabs (load after Core since they call into the registration API on it).
Tabs\Welcome.lua
Tabs\Callback.lua
Tabs\Events.lua
Tabs\Log.lua
Tabs\DB.lua
Tabs\Settings.lua
Tabs\Addon.lua
Tabs\Slash.lua
Tabs\EditMode.lua
Tabs\Locale.lua
Tabs\Hooks.lua
Tabs\Sequencer.lua
Tabs\Timer.lua
Tabs\FSM.lua
Tabs\Comm.lua
Tabs\SmokeTest.lua
